Nomad's chronicles - part 9
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Today I listened to a Menesian prayer addressed to me. I am one of their goddesses, after all.


We never interfere, never communicate with the Menesians.
We ignore their prayers, since they are irrelevant to us.
But this time, the prayer mentioned the monoliths, so I paid attention.


The actual content of the prayer was not important, its form was. The prayer was a song.
It was beautiful and creative, sung by a choir of Menesians, each of them contributing their own voice to the prayer.


The song praised the monoliths as symbols of our godliness.


While listening to the song, I suddenly understood...


